uce limited cases with actual numbers.<br /><br />Right now that commit has no real argument for it except for "do what<br />we do for swap cache". And since we're getting rid of the swap cache<br />special case, I'd say that commit 52d1e606ee73 argues for getting rid<br />of the KSM special case too.<br /><br />Honestly, I'd expect that if KSM is effective, it's for pages that<br />really *are* shared. If you get a lot of "write fault on the last<br />copy" and that ends up being a problem, I think that says more about<br />the KSM issue than it says about the write fault..<br /><br />               Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
